===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Attractive and possessing [[charm]].
#*{{quote-book|year=1963|author={{w|Margery Allingham}}|title={{w|The China Governess}}
|chapter=5|url=http://openlibrary.org/works/OL2004261W
|passage=‘It's rather like a '''beautiful''' Inverness cloak one has inherited. Much too good to hide away, so one wears it instead of an overcoat and pretends it's an amusing new fashion.’}}
#: {{usex|Anyone who has ever met her thought she was absolutely '''beautiful'''.|lang=en}}
#: {{usex|There's a '''beautiful''' lake by the town.|lang=en}}
# {{context|of the weather|lang=en}}&nbsp; Pleasant; clear.
#: {{usex|It's '''beautiful''' outside, let's go for a walk.|lang=en}}
# [[well|Well]] executed.
#: {{usex|The skater performed a '''beautiful''' [[axel]].|lang=en}}
# <!--not an interjection-->(''as a [[pro-sentence]]'')&nbsp; How beautiful that is!
#: {{usex|'''Beautiful'''! What a catch!|lang=en}} (referring to an athlete catching a ball)
# <!--not an interjection-->(''as a pro-sentence; ironic'')&nbsp; How unfortunate that is!
#: {{usex|'''Beautiful'''! I dropped the soup on the floor!|lang=en}}

